title: Executive Order 7236-Charlotte, North Carolina, Little Rock, Arkansas, and Dubuque, Iowa, Abolished as Customs Ports of Entry
content: By virtue of and pursuant to the authority vested in me by the act of August 1, 1914, 38 Stat. 609, 623 (19 U.S.C., sec. 2), the following customs ports of entry in the customs collection districts named are hereby abolished effective 30 days from the date of this order:

Charlotte, North Carolina, customs collection district no. 15 (North Carolina)     Little Rock, Arkansas, customs collection district no. 43 (Tennessee)     Dubuque, Iowa, customs collection district no. 44 (Iowa)
citation: Franklin D. Roosevelt, Executive Order 7236-Charlotte, North Carolina, Little Rock, Arkansas, and Dubuque, Iowa, Abolished as Customs Ports of Entry Online by Gerhard Peters and John T. Woolley, The American Presidency Project https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/node/375213
